# Plan: Fresh Reusable Monorepo Template

## Context

Create a fresh, reusable pnpm monorepo template called `base-template` in `/Users/tim/projects/offline` based on the architecture of `/Users/tim/projects/pbar`. The template includes TanStack Start (web), Expo (mobile), a Node.js API with better-auth + Drizzle, Effect TS for contracts, and shared packages. All CRM-specific business logic is stripped — only the structural skeleton and auth plumbing remain.

The `vendor/effect` directory from pbar is included as-is (local Effect fork).

## Approach

Copy the pbar monorepo structure, then gut all CRM domain code (accounts, opportunities, initiatives, activity, automation, audit, reporting, scorecards, pipeline). Keep: auth flow end-to-end (better-auth, login, session), RBAC system (roles, permissions, middleware, contracts), auth seed data (admin/member/manager users), and project-local agent skills. Replace `@pbar` branding with `@base-template`.

### Naming convention
- Package scope: `@base-template/*`
- App name references: `base-template`

## Structure

```
base-template/
├── .pi/
│   └── skills/         # Project-local agent skills (TanStack, React Doctor, Sweepi)
├── apps/
│   ├── api/            # Node.js HTTP server, better-auth, Drizzle, PostgreSQL, RBAC
│   ├── web/            # TanStack Start + React + TailwindCSS v4
│   └── mobile/         # Expo with expo-router
├── packages/
│   ├── contracts/      # Effect Schema types (auth + RBAC)
│   ├── api-client/     # Typed fetch client (auth only)
│   └── ui/             # Shared theme tokens
├── vendor/
